    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "The vehicle, components and adhesives must be brought to processing temperature (acclimatised) before starting work. The processing temperature must be maintained for 30 minutes before starting to work on the bonding surfaces."
    ,
    
    
    "Bonding surfaces must be free of oil, old adhesive, dirt, moisture, and layers of paint and oxide."
    ,
    
    
    "Silicone and Teflon sprays cannot be used anywhere in the workshop area."
    ,
    
    
    "Body structural adhesive must only be used on bare metal components."
    ,
    
    
    "Only use abrasive products based on pure silicon carbide (SIC) for sanding/grinding down the bonding area until bare."
    ,
    
    
    "Always wear clean gloves when touching the cleaned surfaces to ensure that no sweat from your hands or dirt is transferred onto the bonding surface."
    ,
    
    
    "The joining process must take place directly after applying adhesive in order to guarantee a high quality and reliable bond. Otherwise the adhesive bead must be removed, the surface must be pre-treated and the adhesive must be re-applied."
    ,
    
    
    "After the adhesive has hardened, carefully prime accessible bonding areas and seal with body sealant. Protect bonding areas in cavities from corrosion using cavity preservation."
    
    ]
    
